{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":999,"text":"Last year, I went on my first book tour."},{"time":4271,"text":"In 13 months, I flew to 14 countries"},{"time":7613,"text":"and gave some hundred talks."},{"time":10462,"text":"Every talk in every country"},{"time":12999,"text":"began with an introduction,"},{"time":14999,"text":"and every introduction began,\nalas, with a lie:"},{"time":20567,"text":"\"Taiye Selasi comes\nfrom Ghana and Nigeria,\""},{"time":23912,"text":"or \"Taiye Selasi comes\nfrom England and the States.\""},{"time":28428,"text":"Whenever I heard this opening sentence,"},{"time":30999,"text":"no matter the country that concluded it --"},{"time":33588,"text":"England, America, Ghana, Nigeria --"},{"time":35999,"text":"I thought, \"But that's not true.\""},{"time":39127,"text":"Yes, I was born in England\nand grew up in the United States."},{"time":43436,"text":"My mum, born in England,\nand raised in Nigeria,"},{"time":46807,"text":"currently lives in Ghana."},{"time":48815,"text":"My father was born in Gold Coast,\na British colony,"},{"time":53064,"text":"raised in Ghana,"},{"time":54673,"text":"and has lived for over 30 years\nin the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia."},{"time":58804,"text":"For this reason, my introducers\nalso called me \"multinational.\""},{"time":64498,"text":"\"But Nike is multinational,\" I thought,"},{"time":68490,"text":"\"I'm a human being.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":71124,"text":"Then, one fine day, mid-tour,"},{"time":74308,"text":"I went to Louisiana, a museum in Denmark"},{"time":77808,"text":"where I shared the stage\nwith the writer Colum McCann."},{"time":81580,"text":"We were discussing the role\nof locality in writing,"},{"time":84494,"text":"when suddenly it hit me."},{"time":87157,"text":"I'm not multinational."},{"time":89166,"text":"I'm not a national at all."},{"time":92186,"text":"How could I come from a nation?"},{"time":94999,"text":"How can a human being come from a concept?"},{"time":98745,"text":"It's a question that had been bothering me\nfor going on two decades."},{"time":103403,"text":"From newspapers, textbooks, conversations,"},{"time":106600,"text":"I had learned to speak of countries"},{"time":108886,"text":"as if they were eternal, singular,\nnaturally occurring things,"},{"time":113673,"text":"but I wondered:"},{"time":115554,"text":"to say that I came from a country"},{"time":117350,"text":"suggested that the country\nwas an absolute,"},{"time":120389,"text":"some fixed point in place in time,"},{"time":123095,"text":"a constant thing, but was it?"},{"time":126191,"text":"In my lifetime, countries\nhad disappeared -- Czechoslovakia;"},{"time":130841,"text":"appeared -- Timor-Leste;\nfailed -- Somalia."},{"time":135224,"text":"My parents came from countries\nthat didn't exist when they were born."},{"time":139522,"text":"To me, a country -- this thing that could\nbe born, die, expand, contract --"},{"time":145856,"text":"hardly seemed the basis\nfor understanding a human being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149602,"text":"And so it came as a huge relief\nto discover the sovereign state."},{"time":155232,"text":"What we call countries are actually"},{"time":157194,"text":"various expressions\nof sovereign statehood,"},{"time":159867,"text":"an idea that came into fashion\nonly 400 years ago."},{"time":164295,"text":"When I learned this, beginning my\nmasters degree in international relations,"},{"time":169205,"text":"I felt a sort of surge of relief."},{"time":171598,"text":"It was as I had suspected."},{"time":174352,"text":"History was real, cultures were real,"},{"time":178047,"text":"but countries were invented."},{"time":181022,"text":"For the next 10 years, I sought\nto re- or un-define myself,"},{"time":185507,"text":"my world, my work, my experience,"},{"time":187999,"text":"beyond the logic of the state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190198,"text":"In 2005, I wrote an essay,\n\"What is an Afropolitan,\""},{"time":194761,"text":"sketching out an identity\nthat privileged culture over country."},{"time":200053,"text":"It was thrilling how many people\ncould relate to my experience,"},{"time":204596,"text":"and instructional how many others\ndidn't buy my sense of self."},{"time":210224,"text":"\"How can Selasi claim to come from Ghana,\"\none such critic asked,"},{"time":215248,"text":"\"when she's never known the indignities"},{"time":217540,"text":"of traveling abroad\non a Ghanian passport?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":220777,"text":"Now, if I'm honest,"},{"time":222999,"text":"I knew just what she meant."},{"time":224999,"text":"I've got a friend named Layla\nwho was born and raised in Ghana."},{"time":228472,"text":"Her parents are third-generation\nGhanians of Lebanese descent."},{"time":233506,"text":"Layla, who speaks fluent Twi,\nknows Accra like the back of her hand,"},{"time":238530,"text":"but when we first met years ago,\nI thought, \"She's not from Ghana.\""},{"time":243648,"text":"In my mind, she came from Lebanon,"},{"time":246259,"text":"despite the patent fact\nthat all her formative experience"},{"time":249999,"text":"took place in suburban Accra."},{"time":252376,"text":"I, like my critics,"},{"time":254742,"text":"was imagining some Ghana\nwhere all Ghanaians had brown skin"},{"time":260296,"text":"or none held U.K. passports."},{"time":263219,"text":"I'd fallen into the limiting trap"},{"time":265450,"text":"that the language of coming\nfrom countries sets --"},{"time":268645,"text":"the privileging of a fiction,\nthe singular country,"},{"time":272400,"text":"over reality: human experience."},{"time":276363,"text":"Speaking with Colum McCann that day,\nthe penny finally dropped."},{"time":281433,"text":"\"All experience is local,\" he said."},{"time":284788,"text":"\"All identity is experience,\" I thought."},{"time":288836,"text":"\"I'm not a national,\"\nI proclaimed onstage."},{"time":292710,"text":"\"I'm a local. I'm multi-local.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":295876,"text":"See, \"Taiye Selasi comes\nfrom the United States,\" isn't the truth."},{"time":300452,"text":"I have no relationship\nwith the United States,"},{"time":303253,"text":"all 50 of them, not really."},{"time":305831,"text":"My relationship is with Brookline,\nthe town where I grew up;"},{"time":309638,"text":"with New York City, where I started work;"},{"time":312203,"text":"with Lawrenceville,\nwhere I spend Thanksgiving."},{"time":315797,"text":"What makes America home for me\nis not my passport or accent,"},{"time":321061,"text":"but these very particular experiences"},{"time":323721,"text":"and the places they occur."},{"time":326076,"text":"Despite my pride in Ewe culture,"},{"time":328831,"text":"the Black Stars,\nand my love of Ghanaian food,"},{"time":331999,"text":"I've never had a relationship\nwith the Republic of Ghana, writ large."},{"time":336738,"text":"My relationship is with Accra,\nwhere my mother lives,"},{"time":340417,"text":"where I go each year,"},{"time":342052,"text":"with the little garden in Dzorwulu\nwhere my father and I talk for hours."},{"time":347209,"text":"These are the places\nthat shape my experience."},{"time":350607,"text":"My experience is where I'm from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353999,"text":"What if we asked, instead\nof \"Where are you from?\" --"},{"time":357782,"text":"\"Where are you a local?\""},{"time":359610,"text":"This would tell us so much more\nabout who and how similar we are."},{"time":364047,"text":"Tell me you're from France,\nand I see what, a set of clichés?"},{"time":368655,"text":"Adichie's dangerous single story,\nthe myth of the nation of France?"},{"time":373355,"text":"Tell me you're a local of Fez and Paris,"},{"time":376613,"text":"better yet, Goutte d'Or, and I see\na set of experiences."},{"time":381002,"text":"Our experience is where we're from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383999,"text":"So, where are you a local?"},{"time":386070,"text":"I propose a three-step test."},{"time":388601,"text":"I call these the three \"R’s\":\nrituals, relationships, restrictions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394619,"text":"First, think of your daily rituals,\nwhatever they may be:"},{"time":398557,"text":"making your coffee, driving to work,"},{"time":400614,"text":"harvesting your crops,\nsaying your prayers."},{"time":403514,"text":"What kind of rituals are these?"},{"time":405760,"text":"Where do they occur?"},{"time":407237,"text":"In what city or cities in the world\ndo shopkeepers know your face?"},{"time":412582,"text":"As a child, I carried out fairly standard\nsuburban rituals in Boston,"},{"time":416999,"text":"with adjustments made for the rituals\nmy mother brought from London and Lagos."},{"time":421654,"text":"We took off our shoes in the house,"},{"time":423525,"text":"we were unfailingly\npolite with our elders,"},{"time":426239,"text":"we ate slow-cooked, spicy food."},{"time":428865,"text":"In snowy North America,\nours were rituals of the global South."},{"time":434132,"text":"The first time I went to Delhi\nor to southern parts of Italy,"},{"time":437999,"text":"I was shocked by how at home I felt."},{"time":440359,"text":"The rituals were familiar."},{"time":442975,"text":"\"R\" number one, rituals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445578,"text":"Now, think of your relationships,\nof the people who shape your days."},{"time":450065,"text":"To whom do you speak at least once a week,"},{"time":452629,"text":"be it face to face or on FaceTime?"},{"time":455453,"text":"Be reasonable in your assessment;"},{"time":457183,"text":"I'm not talking about\nyour Facebook friends."},{"time":460064,"text":"I'm speaking of the people who shape\nyour weekly emotional experience."},{"time":464371,"text":"My mother in Accra,\nmy twin sister in Boston,"},{"time":466999,"text":"my best friends in New York:"},{"time":469065,"text":"these relationships are home for me."},{"time":471822,"text":"\"R\" number two, relationships."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474665,"text":"We're local where we carry out\nour rituals and relationships,"},{"time":478999,"text":"but how we experience our locality"},{"time":481765,"text":"depends in part on our restrictions."},{"time":485075,"text":"By restrictions, I mean,\nwhere are you able to live?"},{"time":487942,"text":"What passport do you hold?"},{"time":489999,"text":"Are you restricted by, say, racism,\nfrom feeling fully at home where you live?"},{"time":495290,"text":"By civil war, dysfunctional governance,\neconomic inflation,"},{"time":499577,"text":"from living in the locality\nwhere you had your rituals as a child?"},{"time":504396,"text":"This is the least sexy of the R’s,"},{"time":507017,"text":"less lyric than rituals and relationships,"},{"time":509999,"text":"but the question takes us past\n\"Where are you now?\""},{"time":513333,"text":"to \"Why aren't you there, and why?\""},{"time":517174,"text":"Rituals, relationships, restrictions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520503,"text":"Take a piece of paper"},{"time":522052,"text":"and put those three words\non top of three columns,"},{"time":525368,"text":"then try to fill those columns\nas honestly as you can."},{"time":529041,"text":"A very different picture\nof your life in local context,"},{"time":533226,"text":"of your identity as a set of experiences,"},{"time":536664,"text":"may emerge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537848,"text":"So let's try it."},{"time":539088,"text":"I have a friend named Olu."},{"time":540877,"text":"He's 35 years old."},{"time":542496,"text":"His parents, born in Nigeria,\ncame to Germany on scholarships."},{"time":546465,"text":"Olu was born in Nuremberg\nand lived there until age 10."},{"time":550050,"text":"When his family moved to Lagos,\nhe studied in London,"},{"time":552867,"text":"then came to Berlin."},{"time":554316,"text":"He loves going to Nigeria --"},{"time":556999,"text":"the weather, the food, the friends --"},{"time":559657,"text":"but hates the political corruption there."},{"time":562655,"text":"Where is Olu from?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":564426,"text":"I have another friend named Udo."},{"time":566641,"text":"He's also 35 years old."},{"time":568624,"text":"Udo was born in Córdoba,\nin northwest Argentina,"},{"time":571847,"text":"where his grandparents migrated\nfrom Germany, what is now Poland,"},{"time":575059,"text":"after the war."},{"time":576511,"text":"Udo studied in Buenos Aires,\nand nine years ago came to Berlin."},{"time":580417,"text":"He loves going to Argentina -- \nthe weather, the food, the friends --"},{"time":584642,"text":"but hates the economic corruption there."},{"time":587467,"text":"Where is Udo from?"},{"time":589429,"text":"With his blonde hair and blue eyes,\nUdo could pass for German,"},{"time":593086,"text":"but holds an Argentinian passport,\nso needs a visa to live in Berlin."},{"time":597166,"text":"That Udo is from Argentina\nhas largely to do with history."},{"time":601499,"text":"That he's a local\nof Buenos Aires and Berlin,"},{"time":604680,"text":"that has to do with life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606774,"text":"Olu, who looks Nigerian,\nneeds a visa to visit Nigeria."},{"time":610999,"text":"He speaks Yoruba with an English accent,"},{"time":613414,"text":"and English with a German one."},{"time":615517,"text":"To claim that he's\n\"not really Nigerian,\" though,"},{"time":618082,"text":"denies his experience in Lagos,"},{"time":620434,"text":"the rituals he practiced growing up,"},{"time":622641,"text":"his relationship with family and friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625531,"text":"Meanwhile, though Lagos\nis undoubtedly one of his homes,"},{"time":629476,"text":"Olu always feels restricted there,"},{"time":631999,"text":"not least by the fact that he's gay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635228,"text":"Both he and Udo are restricted\nby the political conditions"},{"time":638975,"text":"of their parents' countries,"},{"time":640652,"text":"from living where some of their\nmost meaningful rituals"},{"time":643660,"text":"and relationships occur."},{"time":645634,"text":"To say Olu is from Nigeria\nand Udo is from Argentina"},{"time":649759,"text":"distracts from their common experience."},{"time":651896,"text":"Their rituals, their relationships,\nand their restrictions are the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656146,"text":"Of course, when we ask,\n\"Where are you from?\""},{"time":658584,"text":"we're using a kind of shorthand."},{"time":660529,"text":"It's quicker to say \"Nigeria\"\nthan \"Lagos and Berlin,\""},{"time":664916,"text":"and as with Google Maps,\nwe can always zoom in closer,"},{"time":668771,"text":"from country to city to neighborhood."},{"time":671255,"text":"But that's not quite the point."},{"time":674310,"text":"The difference between\n\"Where are you from?\""},{"time":676923,"text":"and \"Where are you a local?\""},{"time":678463,"text":"isn't the specificity of the answer;"},{"time":681449,"text":"it's the intention of the question."},{"time":684040,"text":"Replacing the language of nationality\nwith the language of locality asks us"},{"time":689206,"text":"to shift our focus\nto where real life occurs."},{"time":693349,"text":"Even that most glorious expression\nof countryhood, the World Cup,"},{"time":697590,"text":"gives us national teams comprised\nmostly of multilocal players."},{"time":703659,"text":"As a unit of measurement\nfor human experience,"},{"time":706200,"text":"the country doesn't quite work."},{"time":708999,"text":"That's why Olu says, \"I'm German,\nbut my parents come from Nigeria.\""},{"time":713249,"text":"The \"but\" in that sentence\nbelies the inflexibility of the units,"},{"time":718629,"text":"one fixed and fictional entity\nbumping up against another."},{"time":723164,"text":"\"I'm a local of Lagos and Berlin,\"\nsuggests overlapping experiences,"},{"time":727610,"text":"layers that merge together,\nthat can't be denied or removed."},{"time":732176,"text":"You can take away my passport,"},{"time":734432,"text":"but you can't take away my experience."},{"time":736563,"text":"That I carry within me."},{"time":738698,"text":"Where I'm from comes wherever I go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742253,"text":"To be clear, I'm not suggesting\nthat we do away with countries."},{"time":745645,"text":"There's much to be said\nfor national history,"},{"time":747803,"text":"more for the sovereign state."},{"time":749788,"text":"Culture exists in community,\nand community exists in context."},{"time":754509,"text":"Geography, tradition, collective memory:\nthese things are important."},{"time":759006,"text":"What I'm questioning is primacy."},{"time":761999,"text":"All of those introductions on tour\nbegan with reference to nation,"},{"time":766687,"text":"as if knowing what country I came\nfrom would tell my audience who I was."},{"time":771510,"text":"What are we really seeking, though,\nwhen we ask where someone comes from?"},{"time":775439,"text":"And what are we really seeing\nwhen we hear an answer?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":778999,"text":"Here's one possibility:"},{"time":780294,"text":"basically, countries represent power."},{"time":783588,"text":"\"Where are you from?\"\nMexico. Poland. Bangladesh. Less power."},{"time":788671,"text":"America. Germany. Japan. More power."},{"time":792189,"text":"China. Russia. Ambiguous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795703,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":797387,"text":"It's possible that without realizing it,\nwe're playing a power game,"},{"time":801072,"text":"especially in the context\nof multi-ethnic countries."},{"time":804437,"text":"As any recent immigrant knows,"},{"time":806731,"text":"the question \"Where are you from?\"\nor \"Where are you really from?\""},{"time":810999,"text":"is often code for \"Why are you here?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":814324,"text":"Then we have the scholar\nWilliam Deresiewicz's writing"},{"time":817460,"text":"of elite American colleges."},{"time":819257,"text":"\"Students think that\ntheir environment is diverse"},{"time":822432,"text":"if one comes from Missouri\nand another from Pakistan --"},{"time":825711,"text":"never mind that all of their parents\nare doctors or bankers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":830114,"text":"I'm with him."},{"time":831297,"text":"To call one student American,\nanother Pakistani,"},{"time":834792,"text":"then triumphantly claim\nstudent body diversity"},{"time":838077,"text":"ignores the fact that these students\nare locals of the same milieu."},{"time":841744,"text":"The same holds true on the other end\nof the economic spectrum."},{"time":845593,"text":"A Mexican gardener in Los Angeles\nand a Nepali housekeeper in Delhi"},{"time":850289,"text":"have more in common\nin terms of rituals and restrictions"},{"time":854136,"text":"than nationality implies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855946,"text":"Perhaps my biggest problem\nwith coming from countries"},{"time":859565,"text":"is the myth of going back to them."},{"time":861303,"text":"I'm often asked if I plan\nto \"go back\" to Ghana."},{"time":864422,"text":"I go to Accra every year,\nbut I can't \"go back\" to Ghana."},{"time":868766,"text":"It's not because I wasn't born there."},{"time":870591,"text":"My father can't go back, either."},{"time":872948,"text":"The country in which he was born,"},{"time":874999,"text":"that country no longer exists."},{"time":877357,"text":"We can never go back to a place\nand find it exactly where we left it."},{"time":881216,"text":"Something, somewhere\nwill always have changed,"},{"time":884088,"text":"most of all, ourselves."},{"time":886738,"text":"People."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887985,"text":"Finally, what we're talking\nabout is human experience,"},{"time":890556,"text":"this notoriously and gloriously\ndisorderly affair."},{"time":894888,"text":"In creative writing,\nlocality bespeaks humanity."},{"time":898310,"text":"The more we know\nabout where a story is set,"},{"time":900611,"text":"the more local color and texture,"},{"time":902999,"text":"the more human\nthe characters start to feel,"},{"time":905500,"text":"the more relatable, not less."},{"time":907800,"text":"The myth of national identity\nand the vocabulary of coming from"},{"time":912268,"text":"confuses us into placing ourselves\ninto mutually exclusive categories."},{"time":917254,"text":"In fact, all of us are multi --\nmulti-local, multi-layered."},{"time":921583,"text":"To begin our conversations\nwith an acknowledgement of this complexity"},{"time":925391,"text":"brings us closer together, I think,\nnot further apart."},{"time":928996,"text":"So the next time that I'm introduced,"},{"time":932322,"text":"I'd love to hear the truth:"},{"time":934195,"text":"\"Taiye Selasi is a human being,\nlike everybody here."},{"time":938226,"text":"She isn't a citizen of the world,\nbut a citizen of worlds."},{"time":942308,"text":"She is a local of New York,\nRome and Accra.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":945411,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946596,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}